  <body>
    <segment id="1">

Lost trust</segment>
    <segment id="12" parent="25" relname="conjunction">

Germany is on the verge of a recession,</segment>
    <segment id="13" parent="25" relname="conjunction"> 

and the outlook is becoming increasingly bleak.</segment>
    <segment id="2" parent="24" relname="list">  

The economy stopped moving in the second quarter of the current year.</segment>
    <segment id="3" parent="24" relname="list">  

Growth is not expected to pick up again in the third quarter, the results of which will be presented today.</segment>
    <segment id="4" parent="5" relname="reason">  

In addition to these more objective numbers, there are now the subjective ones - the individual expectations.</segment>
    <segment id="5" parent="23" relname="span"> 

And things are looking worse and worse.</segment>
    <segment id="6" parent="22" relname="span">  

Because now the entrepreneurs have also lost courage.</segment>
    <segment id="7" parent="6" relname="evidence"> 

According to the Munich Business Climate Index, they assess the prospects for the next six months to be worse than they were in September.</segment>
    <segment id="8" parent="19" relname="reason"> 


But business is based on trust.</segment>
    <segment id="9" parent="14" relname="condition">  

If companies see no prospects,</segment>
    <segment id="14" parent="19" relname="span"> 

they postpone their investments.</segment>
    <segment id="10" parent="21" relname="span">  

This is alarming,</segment>
    <segment id="15" parent="18" relname="list"> 

especially since private consumption, which was still strong in the first half of the year, has weakened.</segment>
    <segment id="11" parent="17" relname="span">  

At the same time, exports have collapsed,</segment>
    <segment id="16" parent="11" relname="e-elaboration"> 

which have traditionally boosted the German economy.</segment>
<group id="17" type="span" parent="18" relname="list" />
